snippet.textDisplay:
This game of the year is going to be fucking stacked - each of these games are absolutely incredible and deserve GOTY.

The Monke game that brought our boy DK and girl Pauline back into the spotlight .
The Game that is unapologetically Kojima and the sequel to his studios first game after leaving Konami.
The sequel to one of the best Rogue Likes every made that improved upon everything it's predecessor laid out.
The Medieval game that did it's own thing, pushed past it's controversies, improved itself and now landed itself on the most prestigious gaming show competing for GOTY. 
 The Bug game that people waited for patiently , has some of the most dedicated fanbase I've ever seen in a video game and BROKE ALL DIGITAL STORES ..INCLUDING STEAM.
The Game with humble beginnings that defied all odds, and it's very conception is fueled by a singular goal. To make the game THEY wanted to make and redefined the genre along the way.

This year feels particularly special - nothing here feels corporatized - it's just 6 Studios who gave it their all making the best game they possibly could. 
I love video games so fucking much.
